article.headline: Hawaii 60, Nevada 53
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Michael Kuebler scored 23 points to lead Hawaii to a 60-53 victory over Nevada in a Western Athletic Conference game Monday night. Phil Martin and Julian Sensley each added 10 points for Hawaii (9-3, 1-1 WAC). Kirk Snyder, who was held in check for most of the game by Martin, finished with 22 points to lead Nevada (7-4, 1-1). Hawaii took its largest lead at 45-35 on a basket by Jason Carter midway through the second half. The Wolf Pack answered with a 6-0 run, courtesy of four consecutive Hawaii turnovers, that closed the gap to 45-41 with 7:35 remaining. Nevada closed to four again at 49-45 with 6:19 left but the Wolf Pack managed just three more field goals the rest of the game. Hawaii led 31-27 at halftime after using a 15-2 run to rally from a nine-point deficit to close out the first half. Nevada, which made just one field goal in the final eight minutes of the first half, turned the ball over four times and made just two shots in the first eight minutes of the second half.
